"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578761","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-16","<p>The table below shows the number of passengers at airports in northern England flying to/from Heathrow, Gatwick or Schiphol in 2015.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Heathrow</p></td><td><p>Gatwick</p></td><td><p>Amsterdam Schiphol</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Passengers (arrivals and departures)</p></td><td><p>1,430,000</p></td><td><p>29,000</p></td><td><p>1,939,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Figures have been rounded to the nearest 1,000.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578761/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T11:22:16.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578761/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578761/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-08","Aviation: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many passengers from airports across northern England travelled to (a) Heathrow, (b) Gatwick and (c) Schiphol Airport in 2015.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578762","Women and Equalities","false","2016-09-15","<p>On 7 July 2016, the Government responded to the Women and Equalities Select Committee inquiry on transgender equality. In this, we committed to publishing an update on progress against “Working for Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender Equality: Moving Forward (2011)”; and “Advancing transgender equality: a plan for action (2011)”.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will publish both of these documents in due course.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578762/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T17:39:59.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578762/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578762/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-09-08","LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, with reference to page eight of the Government's response to the First Report of the Women and Equalities Committee of Session 2015-16, on Transgender Equality, HC 390, by what date the Government plans to publish an update report on both the existing Transgender Action Plan and the 2011 LGBT Action Plan which includes LGB as well as transgender commitments.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","45657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578763","Cabinet Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>As I stated on 7 September 2016, Official Report, Column 318, the Government is determined that those whose personal safety would be at risk if their details appeared on the register should be able to register anonymously. The Government is aware of concerns that it is difficult for victims of domestic violence to apply for anonymous registration and has announced plans to look closely at the regulations on this important policy.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578763/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T15:33:17.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578763/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578763/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-09-08","Electoral Register: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will ensure that residents of women's refuges are automatically entitled to anonymity on the electoral register.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","45606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578764","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-13","<p>The security of claimant information is a crucial part of the way that data is managed in the department. The personal details of Universal Credit claimants are securely stored and access to this data is strictly controlled. A range of controls are present within the Universal Credit service to protect the confidentiality and integrity of claimant personal data and there are regular tests against these controls to ensure that they meet Government and international security standards.</p><p> </p><p>The Department operates a discretionary special payment scheme. The policy and guiding principles of the scheme are described in Financial Redress for Maladministration which is available on Gov.UK.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/422425/financial-redress-maladministration-apr-15.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/422425/financial-redress-maladministration-apr-15.pdf</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578764/answer",,,,,"45601","2016-09-13T13:36:37.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578764/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578764/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-08","Universal Credit: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the security of the data held in the universal credit system; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","45602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578765","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-13","<p>The security of claimant information is a crucial part of the way that data is managed in the department. The personal details of Universal Credit claimants are securely stored and access to this data is strictly controlled. A range of controls are present within the Universal Credit service to protect the confidentiality and integrity of claimant personal data and there are regular tests against these controls to ensure that they meet Government and international security standards.</p><p> </p><p>The Department operates a discretionary special payment scheme. The policy and guiding principles of the scheme are described in Financial Redress for Maladministration which is available on Gov.UK.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/422425/financial-redress-maladministration-apr-15.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/422425/financial-redress-maladministration-apr-15.pdf</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578765/answer",,,,,"45602","2016-09-13T13:36:37.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578765/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578765/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-08","Universal Credit: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in what circumstances compensation will be made available to universal credit claimants as a result of a breach of security that has been found to compromise their data.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","45601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578766","HM Treasury","false","2016-09-13","<p>HM Revenue and Customs replied to the hon. Member’s letter on 12<sup>th</sup> September 2016.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578766/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T14:50:03.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578766/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578766/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-09-08","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when his Department plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for Walsall North of 17 August 2016 to the Director General, Benefits and Credits, on tax credits and Concentrix related to a constituency case.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","45596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578767","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-13","<p>All tenants in supported accommodation are exempted from the Local Housing Allowance cap until April 2017.</p><p>The Secretary of State has confirmed that the Government expects to make an announcement on the way forward for supported housing in early autumn.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578767/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T11:01:28.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578767/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578767/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-08","Local Housing Allowance: Refuges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that the housing benefit cap does not have an adverse financial effect on refuges for domestic violence survivors; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","45659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578768","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-13","<p>I refer the hon. Gentleman to my previous answer I gave on the 12<sup>th</sup> September 2016 to Question: UIN 44305</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578768/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T14:40:24.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578768/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578768/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-08","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make an assessment of the ability of companies to fund their long-term pension obligations after the reduction in the Bank of England base rate to 0.25 per cent.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","45590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578769","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Secretary of State has confirmed that the Government expects to make an announcement on the way forward for supported housing in early autumn.</p><p>Full impact and equality impact assessments will be undertaken in due course.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578769/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T10:48:33.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578769/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578769/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-08","Housing Benefit: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the housing benefit cap on the ability of people with severe mental illness to afford suitable housing.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","45617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578770","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-23","<p>The Energy Heros scheme is operated by E.ON independently of Government. We do not hold information on it.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578770/answer",,,,,"45688","2016-09-23T13:34:20.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578770/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578770/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Energy: Low Incomes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what financial support his Department provides under the Energy Heroes scheme run by E.ON in (a) England, (b) the North West of England and (c) Denton and Reddish constituency.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","45689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578771","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-16","<p>The UK obtains excellent value from its investment as a member of the European Space Agency (ESA), allowing UK scientists to engage in world-class science in earth observation, space science, exploration, robotics and microgravity research, and providing significant commercial opportunities for UK industry.</p><p>The UK’s investment in ESA enables our involvement in research programmes like the Rosetta-Philae mission (the first ever landing on a comet) and the GAIA mission (mapping the galaxy in an unprecedented level of detail.</p><p>In addition to our investments through ESA, the UK also funds a National Programme, whose budget has grown from around £20m p.a. when the Agency was established on 1<sup>st</sup> April 2011, to £88m p.a..</p><p>The Government protected funding for space in cash terms in the recent spending review, and both our investment in ESA, and our National Space Programme, support the development of the UK space sector, which is growing at a much faster rate than the economy as a whole.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578771/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T13:54:29.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578771/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578771/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Space Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will pursue an expanded national space programme alongside the UK's contribution to the European Space Agency.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","45694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578772","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-20","<p>The Government continues to make progress in securing investment in clean, secure energy, as with the recent announcement on Hinkley Point C. We are committed to ensuring that the UK remains an attractive destination for investment in the coming years.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578772/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-20T13:49:38.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578772/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578772/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Energy: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to improve investor confidence in the UK energy sector.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","45625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578773","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-16","<p>The fundamentals of Britain’s economy are strong. Leaving the EU provides an opportunity for even greater openness with international partners, including Europe. The Government remains committed to making Britain the best place in Europe to grow a business and to achieve this, we will support industry and encourage Foreign Direct Investment.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578773/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T10:52:06.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578773/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578773/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment the Government has made of the potential effect on UK business of the UK's decision to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","45593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578774","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-21","<p>In the four months since the introduction of the advertising provisions in the Conduct of Employment Agencies and Employment Businesses (Amendment) Regulations 2016, EAS has not issued any warning letters to employment agencies or employment businesses in relation to these specific provisions. There have been no prosecutions.</p><p> </p><p>EAS inspectors review advertising records during the course of inspections of employment agencies and employment businesses to ensure compliance with these provisions.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578774/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-21T10:15:31.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578774/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578774/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Employment Agencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many employment agencies and businesses the Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate has (a) issued warning letters to and (b) prosecuted for publishing job advertisements in EEA states before publishing them in the UK since the Conduct of Employment Agencies and Employment Businesses (Amendment) Regulations 2016 came into force; and how his Department plans to monitor the effectiveness of those regulations.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","45768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578775","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-16","<p>Business rates are based on valuations from the Valuation Office Agency and we do not intervene in their independent assessments. We will look closely at the impacts of the forthcoming revaluation and consult on how to make sure the right support is in place for ratepayers to adjust to any changes.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578775/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T15:41:41.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578775/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578775/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-08","Solar Power: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to reduce the planned increases in business rates on solar rooftops from April 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","45728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578776","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-16","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) transferred its responsibilities and resources to the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy in full.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578776/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T13:54:49.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578776/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578776/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, (a) how much funding and (b) how many full-time equivalent staff will be transferred to his Department from the Department for Energy and Climate Change upon the conclusion of the process of merging that Department with his Department.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","45725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578777","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-19","<p>Solar has been deployed rapidly in recent years from low levels with almost 11 GW of capacity now installed.</p><p>Changes to the Feed-in Tariff scheme were introduced in 2016 to manage costs and ensure value for money. While it is appropriate to allow for a period of stability following these changes, we continue to keep the performance of the scheme under review.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578777/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T15:46:24.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578777/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/578777/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-08","Solar Power: Feed-in Tariffs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he plans to take to improve the performance of the feed-in tariff scheme for solar power; and what the timetable for such improvements is.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","45734"
