"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577470","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Triennial Review of Stakes and Prizes is due to be published shortly, and will consider stakes and prizes of all gaming machines.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577470/answer",,,,,"45536 ; 45538","2016-09-12T16:04:02.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577470/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577470/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-07","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make it her policy that licensing of betting premises with fixed odds betting terminals having a maximum stake of more than £10 should be devolved to local authorities in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","45539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577471","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-13","<p>DCMS provides toilet facilities for all staff and visitors.</p><p>Transgender staff or visitors are free to use whichever facilities they choose based on the gender they most identify with.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577471/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T15:31:48.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577471/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577471/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-07","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Sanitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what toilet facilities her Department provides for transgender people.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","45460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577472","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Ships' Names and Badges Committee (SNBC) is responsible for considering and assessing the possible names for a new ship or class of ship. The committee considers all names which have been proposed, formally and informally, and presents its recommendations to a Panel of Senior Naval Officers from the Navy Board. The name(s) chosen at that stage are forwarded to my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence before being submitted to Her Majesty the Queen for final approval.</p><p>A decision with regards to this process is not expected until the Type 26 Global Combat Ship programme has completed its assessment phase and Main Gate.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577472/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T14:51:47.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577472/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577472/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department plans to make a decision on the (a) theme and (b) names of the Type 26 Global Combat Ships.","false","Biography information for Richard Graham","Gloucester","Richard Graham","45442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577473","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>The UK and US have routine discussions on all aspects of US Visiting Forces in the UK. RAF Fairford is a US Visiting Forces base which is held in readiness to receive US and NATO forces as required, and proposed deployments to the base are subject to a process of notification and consultation with the Ministry of Defence. In 2015, as part of the US European Basing Review, the US reiterated that RAF Fairford has a viable long-term future supporting US and NATO requirements.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577473/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T14:51:15.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577473/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577473/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","RAF Fairford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department plans to activate RAF Fairford for use by US visiting forces; and whether he (a) has had or (b) intends to have discussions with the US authorities about the future of RAF Fairford.","false","Biography information for Fabian Hamilton","Leeds North East","Fabian Hamilton","45434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577474","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>No recent discussions have taken place with the Secretary of State for Health regarding gulf war syndrome.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence continues to keep a watching brief on gulf veterans illness but in line with the Medical Research Council review of 2003 has no plans to institute further research either on causation or clinical management.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577474/answer",,,,,"45528","2016-09-13T14:56:04.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577474/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577474/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Gulf War Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Health on Gulf War Syndrome.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","45527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577475","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>No recent discussions have taken place with the Secretary of State for Health regarding gulf war syndrome.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence continues to keep a watching brief on gulf veterans illness but in line with the Medical Research Council review of 2003 has no plans to institute further research either on causation or clinical management.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577475/answer",,,,,"45527","2016-09-13T14:56:04.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577475/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577475/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Gulf War Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department plans to fund further research into Gulf War Syndrome.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","45528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577477","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Government takes these allegations very seriously. We have analysed the case carefully and raised the issue with the Saudi-led Coalition.</p><p> </p><p>The key test for our continued arms exports to Saudi Arabia in relation to International Humanitarian Law (IHL) is whether there is a clear risk that those weapons might be used in a serious violation of IHL. This is kept under careful and continual review.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577477/answer",,,,,"45960","2016-10-13T15:06:31.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577477/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577477/answer","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577477/answer/previousversion/12060","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Yemen: Cluster Munitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 5 July 2016 to Question 41376, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of evidence provided by Amnesty International on the alleged use of UK-produced BL-755 cluster munitions by the Saudi-led Coalition in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","45513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577478","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>In 2015-16, the Ministry of Defence placed 320 new contracts with suppliers that were assessed through the Dun and Bradstreet process as small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). These had a total value of around £206 million. A further 435 contracts, with a total value of around £8,748 million, were placed with suppliers whose SME status has not currently been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.</p><p> </p><p>The Crown Commercial Service contract that identifies and assesses the SME status of suppliers through the Dun and Bradstreet process expired in 2014. As a result, while we hold management information about our expenditure with all contracted suppliers, we do not currently hold accurate information on the SME status of the 435 contracted suppliers that have not been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions are under way with the Crown Commercial Service and across Government to re-introduce this service, with a view to retrospective assessments being completed. This means that the above figures are provisional and subject to change.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577478/answer",,,,,"45553 ; 45574","2016-09-12T14:43:28.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577478/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577478/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's Finance and Economics Annual Bulletin: Trade, Industry and Contracts 2016, published on 25 August 2016, what information his Department holds on the SME status of the suppliers who were awarded contracts in 2015-16 but whose SME status was not assessed by Dun and Bradstreet on behalf of his Department.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","45575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577479","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>In 2015-16, the Ministry of Defence placed 320 new contracts with suppliers that were assessed through the Dun and Bradstreet process as small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). These had a total value of around £206 million. A further 435 contracts, with a total value of around £8,748 million, were placed with suppliers whose SME status has not currently been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.</p><p> </p><p>The Crown Commercial Service contract that identifies and assesses the SME status of suppliers through the Dun and Bradstreet process expired in 2014. As a result, while we hold management information about our expenditure with all contracted suppliers, we do not currently hold accurate information on the SME status of the 435 contracted suppliers that have not been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions are under way with the Crown Commercial Service and across Government to re-introduce this service, with a view to retrospective assessments being completed. This means that the above figures are provisional and subject to change.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577479/answer",,,,,"45553 ; 45575","2016-09-12T14:43:29.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577479/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577479/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's Finance and Economics Annual Bulletin: Trade, Industry and Contracts 2016, published on 25 August 2016, what estimate he has made of the total (a) number and (b) value of contracts placed by his Department with SMEs in 2015-16, including the 435 contracts placed with suppliers whose SME status was not assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","45574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577480","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Office for National Statistics (ONS) and the Ministry of Defence have established a working group to review the decision not to record veteran Service personnel in the 2021 census. To date it has met five times. The working group is developing a number of themes which has allowed us to develop a good understanding of each other's needs.</p><p>The ONS will be inviting key stakeholders from across Government, Local Authorities and the charitable sector to a meeting this autumn to further seek their input. In addition both organisations met with the Royal British Legion in July this year to explain the work that both departments are taking forward</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577480/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T14:54:50.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577480/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577480/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Veterans: Census","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what information his Department holds on progress made by the Office for National Statistics in reviewing its decision not to record veteran service personnel in the 2021 census since his letter of 12 July 2016.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","45552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577481","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>On 12 May 2016, the then Minister for the Armed Forces (Penny Mordaunt) made a written ministerial statement (HCWS 726) which announced that the five year UK residency requirement was being waived to allow for 200 Commonwealth citizens per annum to be recruited to fill a limited number of roles in the Regular Armed Forces which require specialist skills. The limit and the list of roles that can be filled under these arrangements were agreed in consultation with the Home Office. Those Commonwealth citizens who do not have the required skills to fill one of the 200 specialist roles are still required to meet the five year UK residency requirement.</p><p>Since the written statement, some 9,500 applications for specialist roles have been received from Commonwealth citizens. Many applicants will be rejected for not meeting the relevant eligibility criteria, or will fail the various stages of the selection process. The numbers who are enlisted and then successfully complete the training to fill one of these roles will therefore not exceed the 200 per annum limit.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577481/answer","20160512_WMS_Commonwealth_Recruitment.docx","20160512_WMS_Commonwealth_Recruitment.docx","20160512 WMS - Commonwealth Recruitment","20160512 WMS - Commonwealth Recruitment","45778","2016-09-13T14:57:19.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577481/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577481/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people applied for the 200 support role vacancies advertised by his Department in May 2016 when it waived the five year British citizenship rule for Commonwealth recruits.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","45549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577482","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Forces Help to Buy Scheme continues to prove popular amongst members of the Armed Forces.</p><p>The latest monthly figures for the Forces Help to Buy Scheme are published at the following address:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/546417/20160818-FHTB_Official_Stats_July.pdf</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577482/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T14:54:26.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577482/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577482/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Forces Help to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's announcement of 4 October 2015, on the Forces Help to Buy Scheme, whether his Department is on target to achieve an uptake of 10,000 of that scheme by October 2016.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","45550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577483","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>In 2015-16, the Ministry of Defence placed 320 new contracts with suppliers that were assessed through the Dun and Bradstreet process as small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). These had a total value of around £206 million. A further 435 contracts, with a total value of around £8,748 million, were placed with suppliers whose SME status has not currently been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.</p><p> </p><p>The Crown Commercial Service contract that identifies and assesses the SME status of suppliers through the Dun and Bradstreet process expired in 2014. As a result, while we hold management information about our expenditure with all contracted suppliers, we do not currently hold accurate information on the SME status of the 435 contracted suppliers that have not been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions are under way with the Crown Commercial Service and across Government to re-introduce this service, with a view to retrospective assessments being completed. This means that the above figures are provisional and subject to change.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577483/answer",,,,,"45574 ; 45575","2016-09-12T14:43:28.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577483/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577483/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the SME status of suppliers awarded new contracts by his Department has not been assessed by Dun and Bradstreet since 2014; and if he will commission an independent assessment of the SME status of all suppliers awarded contracts by his Department in 2015-16.","fa