ber 2016, on Defence Estate Rationalisation, HCWS133, how many (a) military and (b) civilian personnel are based at each site.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","45334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577486","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>The UK is proud to be one of five NATO countries that meet the Defence Investment Pledge (DIP) to spend 2% of GDP on Defence. I am pleased with the progress the Alliance has made in reversing the trend in cuts to Defence spending. I reviewed progress with NATO Allies at the Warsaw Summit last July, by which time 16 Allies had increased Defence spending, and eight had committed to reaching the 2% guideline in national plans. Progress will continue to be monitored through regular NATO Defence Ministerial meetings.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577486/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T15:53:36.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577486/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577486/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what representations he has made to his NATO counterparts on meeting their commitment to spend at least two per cent of GDP on defence.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","45335"
