"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577574","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Home Office holds information as to the relevant local authority, responsible adult and social worker for each individual unaccompanied asylum seeking child and we remain in contact with these parties whilst considering the child’s asylum claim. This information is not collated and does not form part of our published statistics.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577574/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T16:07:16.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577574/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577574/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information her Department holds on the geographical distribution by parliamentary constituency of unaccompanied minors who have applied for asylum in the UK in each of the last 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","45436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577575","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>A response to your letter of 17 August 2016 has been sent today.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577575/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T15:25:04.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577575/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577575/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when her Department plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for Walsall North of 17 August 2016 to the Director General, UK Visas and Immigration on visitor visas, constituent case references GWF041254009 and GWF 041254061.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","45355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577576","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>The UK has already committed to resettling 20,000 Syrian refugees from the region during this parliament and we have no plans to increase this at the present time. Our priorities are humanitarian aid and actively seeking an end to the conflict in Syria.</p><p>We believe this approach is the best way to ensure that the UK’s help has the greatest impact for the majority of refugees who remain in the region and their host countries. The government has been working with the Local Government Association, local authorities and devolved administrations across the UK in order to ensure we have the capacity and infrastructure to meet our commitment to resettle 20,000 vulnerable Syrians by the end of this Parliament.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577576/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T15:23:22.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577576/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577576/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to work with the Local Government Association to explore the possibility of accommodating more than 20,000 Syrian refugees by 2020.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","45385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577577","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement scheme is voluntary and there has been a tremendous amount of goodwill from local authorities. Some of those authorities have not resettled people in the initial phases of the scheme, but will be resettling people in the future. We ask local authorities who have pledged their help be sure they have the infrastructure and support networks needed to ensure the appropriate care and integration of these refugees before telling us how many individuals they believe they are able to resettle. Once a local authority has pledged to resettle refugees – however many – we work with them to ensure there are suitable accommodation and care packages in place in that authority area in order for resettlement to take place. We will only place individuals in a particular area once we’ve ensured these arrangements are in place and will manage the flows based on need and in support of the wellbeing of the people and communities involved.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577577/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T15:24:46.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577577/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577577/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of the Syrian refugees planned to be taken in by the UK by 2020 will be located in each (a) constituent nation and region and (b) local authority area in the UK.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","45386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577578","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Government began work to implement the ‘Dubs amendment’ immediately after the Immigration Bill gained Royal Assent. Over 30 children who meet the criteria in the Immigration Act have been accepted for transfer since it received Royal Assent in May, the majority of these have already arrived in the UK.</p><p>We continue to work with the French, Greek and Italian authorities and others to speed up existing family reunification processes or implement new processes where necessary for unaccompanied children. We have seconded a UK official to Greece; we have a long-standing secondee working in Italy and will shortly be seconding another official to the French Interior Ministry to support these efforts.</p><p>We have established a dedicated team in the Home Office Dublin Unit to lead on family reunion cases for unaccompanied children. Transfer requests under the Dublin Regulation are now generally processed within 10 days and children transferred within weeks. Over 120 children have been accepted for transfer this year from Europe.</p><p>We also continue to consult local authorities about the transfer unaccompanied refugee children from Europe to the UK, where it is in their best interests</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577578/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T16:05:44.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577578/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577578/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent steps she has taken to accelerate the family reunification process for unaccompanied children in Europe.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","45379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577579","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>We will continue to reform the student visa system to tackle abuse, and deliver an effective immigration system that is fair to British citizens and those who play by the rules. At the same time, we continue to be committed to ensuring our top universities are a magnet for the best students from around the world.</p><p>Our immigration rules for non-EU workers already cater for highly skilled workers, including academics, scientists and researchers</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577579/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T16:07:01.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577579/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577579/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Visas: Higher Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will bring forward proposals to amend visa regulations to better support international university staff and student mobility in order to expand UK universities' science and research markets outside of the EU.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","45380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577580","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>In England there are currently (a) 35 Life in the UK centres and (b)17 English Language Test Centres.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577580/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T16:07:42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577580/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577580/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","British Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many test centres there are in England for citizenship applicants to take the (a) life in the UK and (b) English language test.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577581","Home Office","false","2016-09-15","<p>The UK passport is changed every five years for security reasons. The lead time for a re-designed passport is dependent on the level of changes to be made.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577581/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T14:42:24.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577581/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577581/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department has made an assessment of the lead time required for the introduction of a redesigned British passport; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","45361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577582","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Home Office funds strategic migration partnerships which are local authority-led partnerships designed to provide structures and support services for those organisations working with migrants and refugees in local communities.</p><p>The Home Office also provides a dedicated integration loan directly to recognised refugees. The loan is designed to help refugees integrate into UK society by offering financial support towards housing costs, employment and training.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577582/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T13:56:53.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577582/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577582/answer","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577582/answer/previousversion/11022","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to support local authorities in integrating refugees into British society.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","45347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577583","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Home Office is committed to publishing data in an orderly way as part of the regular quarterly Immigration Statistics, in line with the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p><p>Latest statistics published on 25 August confirmed that a total of a total of 2,898 Syrians have been resettled under the scheme since it began, 2,646 of these arriving since 1 October 2015.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577583/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T12:37:47.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577583/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577583/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to publish regular updates on progress on accepting Syrian refugees into the UK.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","45348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577585","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Home Office does not set the target timescales for the return of forensically analysed evidence. This would be an operational matter within policing for each Chief Constable.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577585/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T12:16:12.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577585/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577585/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Forensic Science","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the (a) target and (b) actual average timescale was for the return of forensically analysed evidence in cases involving (i) burglary, (ii) murder, (iii) violence against the person, excluding murder, (iv) drugs offences and (v) sexual offences in the last 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577586","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Home Office undertakes checks to confirm that potential candidates meet the eligibility requirements to work in the UK. However, the Home Office does not record the nationality of employees on our IT systems and is unable to provide this information.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577586/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T16:04:54.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577586/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577586/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Home Office: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many citizens of other EU countries work in her Department, its agencies and non-departmental public bodies.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","45510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577587","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>The investigation and prosecution of individuals suspected of war crimes is an operational matter and any decision to investigate or prosecute is the responsibility of the police in consultation with Crown Prosecution Service. Investigations into these offences are conducted using jointly agreed guidelines between the Crown Prosecution Service and SO15 ; these guidelines can be found on the Crown Prosecution Service website. The Home Office does not issue separate guidance to police forces on investigation of historical war crimes.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577587/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T14:48:39.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577587/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577587/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","War Crimes: Criminal Investigation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance her Department has issued to police services on investigation of historical war crimes.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","45476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577588","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>Figures on asylum applications and decisions for Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children (UASC) are published quarterly by the Home Office in the Immigration Statistics release.</p><p>The attached table shows asylum applications, decisions and grants from Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children, excluding dependants, from Quarter 3 2015 to Quarter 2 2016.</p><p>A copy of the latest release, Immigration Statistics April to June 2016, is available from: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2016</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577588/answer","PQ 45482 Table.xlsx","PQ 45482 Table.xlsx","Asylum application decisions","Asylum application decisions",,"2016-09-12T15:25:29.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577588/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577588/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of unaccompanied minors who have (a) applied for and (b) been granted asylum in the UK in each of the last 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","45482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577589","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Government continues to keep the law on hate crime under review. The Law Commission published a report on hate crime legislation in May 2014. This considered whether existing offences should be extended to other groups not currently covered by the offences and made recommendations including that there should be a full review of the hate crime framework. The Government made a commitment to a review of hate crime legislation in its manifesto and is considering options.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577589/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T14:21:08.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577589/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577589/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to extend the range of hate crimes.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","45441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577590","Home Office","false","2016-09-13","<p>Our immigration rules for non-EU workers already cater for the highly skilled, including academics, scientists and researchers. Within the immigration system, we have consistently protected and enhanced the treatment of such roles, even whilst restricting migration in other spheres.</p><p>In Tier 2, the skilled work route, PhD level roles are given higher priority when allocating places within the annual limit and are exempt from certain of the usual recruitment and settlement rules. The Tier 1 (Exceptional Talent) route is also available for world leaders in science, engineering, humanities, the arts and digital technology, and several universities and research organisations are making use of this route. The Tier 5 (Temporary Work) route contains provisions to enable sponsored researchers to participate in international research collaborations, and for overseas medical and dental post-graduates to undertake training in the UK.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577590/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T16:05:27.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577590/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577590/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Visas: Space Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will bring forward proposals to amend visa regulations to better enable highly skilled people to come to the UK to work in the space and satellite sector.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","45520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577591","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>All non EEA Visitors to the UK are assessed against the requirements set out in appendix V of the Immigration Rules. These are the same for all regardless of nationality.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577591/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T15:24:31.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577591/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577591/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Overseas Visitors: Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the differences are in entry clearance requirements of visitors to the UK from (a) Israel and (b) the occupied Palestinian territories.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","45572"
