"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577609","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-16","<p>The timetabling of necessary pre-trial preparation and the giving of appropriate directions for an effective trial listing is a judicial matter. The parties will advise the court at a preliminary hearing of any issues affecting readiness for trial, including the availability of required forensic evidence, and it rests with the court to make appropriate decisions about the trial date.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577609/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T10:39:26.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577609/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577609/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Forensic Science: Evidence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment she has made of the effect of current timescales for the return of forensic evidence on the length of time court cases are taking to progress.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577610","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-27","<p>The Secretary of State for Justice has not received any representations concerning magistrates’ new e-mail addresses.</p><p> </p><p>The Judiciary worked with the Ministry of Justice Information Assurance team and an Independent CLAS (CESG Listed Advisor Scheme) consultant to produce a technical risk assessment and achieve security accreditation for the service.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577610/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-27T13:55:47.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577610/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577610/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Magistrates: Email","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, (a) what representations she has received and (b) what assessment she has made of the security of magistrates' new e-mail addresses.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577611","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-16","<p>The National Offender Management Service Annual Offender Equalities Report will for the first time include prisoner declaration data in relation to sexual orientation.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577611/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T13:17:03.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577611/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577611/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Prisoners: Homosexuality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate she has made of the (a) number and (b) proportion of (i) male prisoners who are homosexual and (ii) female prisoners who are lesbian.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577612","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-16","<p>The Ministry of Justice plan to publish a report on the use of section 44 of the Mental Capacity Act 2005 in due course.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577612/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T10:34:59.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577612/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577612/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Mental Capacity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when her Department plans to publish the Government's review of Section 44 of the Mental Capacity Act 2005.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","45473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577613","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-14","<p>Anyone facing criminal charges at court is eligible for legal aid, subject to a statutory means test. This ensures more affluent defendants make contributions towards their legal aid costs.</p><p>The information declared by defendants can be verified by cross-referencing data with other government departments, undertaking checks with credit reference agencies and employers and making requests for supporting documentation.</p><p>If the declaration is found to be untrue, we will reassess the defendant’s means and, if necessary, revise the contribution or potentially withdraw legal aid. If we suspect or detect fraudulent activity, we would refer to our special investigations unit who will, if necessary, prosecute and seek to recover costs from applicants.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577613/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T16:13:41.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577613/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577613/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans she has to facilitate financial checks on means forms filled out by offenders in criminal courts.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577614","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-14","<p>The information requested is not available.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577614/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T09:56:28.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577614/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577614/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Suspended Sentences: Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the highest number of suspended sentences that one person had without receiving a prison sentence for committing a further offence during the operational period of those sentences was in a (a) magistrates' court and (b) Crown court in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577615","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-16","<p>The number of men and women who entered prison, by offence type, in each of the last five years is available on gov.uk. The figures relating to the number of previous convictions received by those individuals could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577615/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T12:02:09.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577615/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577615/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Prison Sentences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of (i) male and (ii) female offenders were sent to prison by (A) offence type and (B) number of previous convictions at the time of sentence in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45423"
