"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577617","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-14","<p>The information requested is available on gov.uk using the following link: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015</a></p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577617/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T16:23:40.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577617/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577617/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Pornography: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people of each sex have been (a) cautioned, (b) prosecuted and (c) convicted of an offence under section 33 of the Criminal Justice and Courts Act 2015 for disclosing private sexual photographs or films with intent to cause distress.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577618","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-15","<p>In 2015, of defendants whose cases were completed in the magistrates’ courts, 14% had a date of trial recorded in centrally held data. Of those cases with a trial date recorded, the mean duration from date of first listing to date of trial was 67 days and the median duration was 61 days.</p><p> </p><p>HMCTS does not separately collate timeliness of trials which are effective at their first trial hearing and is unable to provide that information.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577618/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T10:15:48.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577618/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577618/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Magistrates' Courts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average length of time is from first appearance to trial in magistrates' courts in (a) all cases and (b) cases that proceed at the first trial hearing; and what proportion of all trial cases fall into each such category.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577619","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-15","<p>The data requested is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577619/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T10:41:52.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577619/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577619/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Bail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many crimes have been committed by people on post-conviction bail, by each category of offence, in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","45433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577620","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-14","<p>Contingency plans have been prepared in case alternative arrangements are needed.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577620/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T10:02:57.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577620/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577620/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Community Rehabilitation Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether her Department has contingency plans for financial failure of community rehabilitation centres.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","45543"
