"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577630","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-15","<p>Public sector civil servants and those public servants working for accredited Non Departmental Public Bodies (NDPB) have access to vacancies in the National Probation Service (NPS) after they have been advertised to surplus civil servants Vacancies are open to all employees from across the Civil Service regardless of grade or department.</p><p>Arrangements are in place to recognise existing terms and conditions if someone in the wider Civil Service is successful in obtaining a job in the NPS.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577630/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T11:42:11.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577630/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577630/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","National Probation Service for England and Wales: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will review entry to employment in the National Probation Service to (a) enable more public sector staff to access the vacancies in that service and (b) ensure that the previous public sector experience of new applicants is recognised with regard to their terms and conditions.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","45565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577631","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-15","<p>The recruitment of prison officers involves a number of internal and external parties that all contribute towards the overall process.</p><p> </p><p>The cost to the public purse of prison officer recruitment is not held centrally by The National Offender Management Service, and it can only be obtained at a disproportionate cost.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577631/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T11:13:52.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577631/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577631/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-07","Prison Officers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the total cost to the public purse of prison officer recruitment was in each quarter since June 2013.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","45564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577633","Leader of the House","false","2016-09-12","<p>The new e-petitions system has been running for over a year now and the Government is pleased with the level of engagement that it has prompted among the public.</p><p> </p><p>Individual Departments are responsible for the content and timeliness of responses to e-petitions, however the Leader's office has general Government oversight of e-petitions. My predecessor reminded Cabinet colleagues of the importance of quality and timely responses to e-petitions at the beginning of the second session. I will be writing to Cabinet colleagues this week with a similar reminder.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577633/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T16:28:15.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577633/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577633/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2016-09-07","e-Petitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what steps he is taking to improve the quality of Government responses to e-petitions.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","45404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577634","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-09-27","<p>The Government remains committed to introducing greater transparency in the regulation of donations and loans to Northern Ireland political parties and I intend to consult the Northern Ireland parties shortly on this matter.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577634/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-27T14:15:32.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577634/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577634/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-09-07","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will make it his policy to end the anonymity of donations to political parties in Northern Ireland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","45490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577635","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-09-15","<p>Non-nuclear energy is devolved and the delivery of a new interconnector is a matter for the Northern Ireland Executive and the Government of Ireland.</p><p>I have had discussions with Northern Ireland Executive Ministers and the sector on increasing security of supply, lowering energy costs and meeting the UK’s renewables commitments.</p><p>I hope proposals for a new interconnector move forward quickly to deliver a stronger, more secure and more competitive network in Northern Ireland.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577635/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T14:43:57.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577635/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577635/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-09-07","Electricity Interconnectors: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment he has made of progress in negotiations with the Irish Government towards the construction of the North South Electricity Interconnector; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","45462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577636","Prime Minister","false","2016-09-12","<p>Information on Parliamentary Private Secretaries has been published today.</p><p> </p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577636/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T15:33:02.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577636/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577636/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-09-07","Parliamentary Private Secretaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if she will publish a list of Parliamentary Private Secretaries.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","45481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577637","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Government recognises the power of international events to shine a spotlight on the success of cities and towns across the UK. The UK business events industry is thriving, and Government is committed to supporting its continued growth.</p><p><br> Nick de Bois, Chair of the UK Events Industry Board and myself will meet with the hon Member for Denton and Reddish, and representatives of the Greater Manchester Combined Authority, to discuss the ways in which the Government can support Manchester’s business events industry.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577637/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T09:44:29.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577637/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577637/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-07","World Expo: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will meet representatives of the Greater Manchester Combined Authority and the hon. Member for Denton and Reddish to discuss Manchester's bid to host the 2025 World Expo.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","45559"
