"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577914","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-14","<p>It was stated in the letter to which the noble Lord refers that Navy Command was actively considering the out of service dates for both RFA DILIGENCE and RFA ARGUS, as well as the replacement capability. As a result of those considerations, and taking into account DILIGENCE's age and increasing obsolescence, it was concluded that retaining her in service would no longer represent good value for money to the taxpayer, and the decision was taken to retire her early.</p><p>This decision does not detract from the invaluable service that DILIGENCE has provided for over 30 years.</p>",,"Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577914/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T16:23:58.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577914/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577914/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the response by Navy Command Headquarters to a member of the public on 12 February, what new studies in the Ministry of Defence have superseded the statement made in that response that the operational capabilities of both Diligence, as the operational maintenance and repair ship, and Argus, as the primary casualty receiving facility with aviation training capability, are "invaluable to the support of the Royal Navy".","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577915","Department for Education","false","2016-09-19","<p>On 12 August, we published proposals for how apprenticeships will be funded in England from May 2017; these include how apprentices living elsewhere in the UK, but employed in England, will be supported. Details are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/views-sought-on-plans-to-boost-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/views-sought-on-plans-to-boost-apprenticeships</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We are committed to publishing final funding rates and rules for England by the end of October. Discussions are taking place with devolved administrations to ensure that apprenticeship funding works for employers wherever they are in the UK, when the levy is introduced.</p><p> </p><p>The apprenticeship levy will be payable at 0.5% of pay bill by employers across the whole of the UK. An allowance of £15,000 means that only employers with a pay bill of more than £3 million per year will pay the levy, less than 2% of employers. The levy will come into effect on 6 April 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The UK government has made a commitment that the devolved administrations will receive a fair share of the levy, and discussions are ongoing to deliver this outcome. As skills policy is devolved it is for the devolved administrations to decide how they will fund apprenticeships in their nations.</p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577915/answer",,,,,"HL1664","2016-09-19T12:36:05.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577915/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577915/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-09-07","Apprentices: Taxation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they will publish details of how the apprenticeship levy will affect employers in the devolved UK nations.","false","Biography information for Lord Aberdare",,"Lord Aberdare","HL1663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577917","Department for Education","false","2016-09-19","<p>On 12 August, we published proposals for how apprenticeships will be funded in England from May 2017; these include how apprentices living elsewhere in the UK, but employed in England, will be supported. Details are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/views-sought-on-plans-to-boost-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/views-sought-on-plans-to-boost-apprenticeships</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We are committed to publishing final funding rates and rules for England by the end of October. Discussions are taking place with devolved administrations to ensure that apprenticeship funding works for employers wherever they are in the UK, when the levy is introduced.</p><p> </p><p>The apprenticeship levy will be payable at 0.5% of pay bill by employers across the whole of the UK. An allowance of £15,000 means that only employers with a pay bill of more than £3 million per year will pay the levy, less than 2% of employers. The levy will come into effect on 6 April 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The UK government has made a commitment that the devolved administrations will receive a fair share of the levy, and discussions are ongoing to deliver this outcome. As skills policy is devolved it is for the devolved administrations to decide how they will fund apprenticeships in their nations.</p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577917/answer",,,,,"HL1663","2016-09-19T12:36:05.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577917/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577917/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-09-07","Apprentices: Taxation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when employers in the devolved UK nations will start to pay the apprenticeship levy; and how funds raised from that levy will be made available to promote apprenticeships in the devolved nations.","false","Biography information for Lord Aberdare",,"Lord Aberdare","HL1664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577918","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-15","<p>The Secretary of State has received 41 requests from local authorities since September 2013 for permission to sell land at undervalue under section 123 of the Local Government Act 1972. Of the requests received, 25 were granted, 6 were withdrawn, and 7 considered to be either invalid or the Secretary of State declined to determine. The remaining 3 cases are currently under consideration.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577918/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T13:52:26.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577918/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577918/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-07","Local Government: Land","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many requests have been received from local authorities in the last three years for permission to sell land at undervalue under section 123 of the Local Government Act 1972; and whether those requests were granted or refused.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ford",,"Baroness Ford","HL1665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577919","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-15","<p>The Government is committed to addressing the supply of new land for housing. That is why we have set an ambitious commitment to dispose of surplus government-owned land in England with the capacity for at least 160,000 homes by 2020.</p><p>As of the end of June, central government departments and their agencies had identified enough land for approximately 139,000 homes. Of this, land with the capacity for an estimated 11,691 homes has already been disposed of. We will be publishing an annual report setting out detailed progress towards the commitment later this year, and will also monitor the broad progress of development on sites released through the programme. The report will include data showing land released for housing since 2012, broken down by department.</p><p>This builds on our previous Public Sector Land programme in the last Parliament, where between 2011 and 2015, central government departments and their agencies disposed of land with capacity for 109,590 homes.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577919/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T14:02:23.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577919/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577919/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-07","Government Departments: Land","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much public land held by central government departments and their agencies has been disposed of for house building since 2012, broken down by department.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ford",,"Baroness Ford","HL1666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577920","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-15","<p>The local planning authorities piloting the preparation of local brownfield registers were asked to complete their registers by the end of June 2016.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577920/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T14:01:16.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577920/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577920/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-07","Derelict Land","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the target date for the 73 councils across England to complete their brownfield registers.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ford",,"Baroness Ford","HL1667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577921","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-15","<p>Since April 2015, my Department has received three large selective licensing applications from the following local authorities: London Borough of Redbridge, Burnley Borough Council and Peterborough City Council. There are currently no applications pending.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577921/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-15T13:59:03.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577921/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577921/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-07","Landlords: Licensing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which local authorities (1) have applied for Secretary of State consent for discretionary landlord licensing schemes since new rules were introduced in 2015, and (2) have applications pending.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ford",,"Baroness Ford","HL1668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577922","Department for Education","false","2016-09-20","<p>The Government has considered carefully the Tirkey v Chandhok judgment and its implications, including for the caste duty and the Equality Act, and has decided to issue a public consultation on this important and sensitive matter. The consultation will run for 12 weeks from its commencement date. One of the key aims of the consultation will be to obtain the views of stakeholders on the appropriate provision that should be made for caste in the Act.</p><p> </p><p>We are especially keen to hear the public’s views on whether, in light of the Tirkey v Chandok judgment, additional measures are needed to ensure victims of caste discrimination have appropriate legal protection and effective remedies under the 2010 Equality Act.</p><p> </p><p>We will then consider the responses to the consultation very carefully before deciding what further action is most appropriate.</p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577922/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-20T14:02:01.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577922/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577922/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-09-07","Castes: Discrimination","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what form the consultation on section 9(5) of the Equality Act 2010 on caste-based discrimination will take; how they will formulate the questions to be addressed in the consultations; and whether that consultation will be on how section 9(5) can best be brought into effect or on whether it should be brought into effect.","false","Biography information for Lord Harries of Pentregarth",,"Lord Harries of Pentregarth","HL1669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577923","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-19","<p>We were appalled by reports of aid workers coming under attack at the Terrain hotel. It is completely unacceptable to target people who have themselves gone to help those in greatest need. We have strongly condemned this attack and the UN Security Council emphasised concerns about this incident directly to the South Sudanese government during its visit to Juba in early September.</p><p>Together with our Troika colleagues, we urged the South Sudanese authorities to carry out a thorough investigation into the atrocities committed at the Terrain compound; and the UN has launched a special independent investigation into the violence and the response of the UN Mission in South Sudan.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577923/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T09:42:10.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577923/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577923/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","South Sudan: Humanitarian Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of South Sudan following reports of attacks on aid workers at the Terrain hotel in Juba in July; and what action they plan to take alongside the USA to investigate the reported crimes committed.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL1670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577924","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-19","<p>We do not evaluate the operations of other embassies, but we are pleased that the UN have announced that they will launch a special independent investigation into the violence and the response of the UN Mission. Our Embassy in Juba helped all those British Nationals who wanted to leave the country during the recent violence in Juba to do so, while at the same time evacuating our own non-essential staff. We will continue to provide consular assistance to those remaining in country.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577924/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T09:40:58.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577924/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577924/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","South Sudan: Humanitarian Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have evaluated the efficacy of the emergency response of foreign embassies to the reported attacks on aid workers at the Terrain hotel in Juba in July.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL1671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577925","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-19","<p>The welfare of British Nationals in South Sudan is a top priority for our Embassy in Juba. We have advised our citizens to leave but we recognise that some of those working in non-governmental organisations have decided to stay and will continue to provide assistance to them. The reinforced mandate of the UN Mission in South Sudan, including the arrival of a Regional Protection Force in Juba, is designed to provide greater protection for the civilian population, as well as humanitarian agencies and non-governmental organisations. We will continue to lobby the government of South Sudan to allow the mission to operate effectively.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577925/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T09:39:28.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577925/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577925/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","South Sudan: Humanitarian Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the impact of the reported attacks on aid workers in Juba in July on (1) the longer-term presence of UK non-governmental organisations in South Sudan, and (2) the UK's future relations with the government of South Sudan.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL1672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577926","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-12","<p>There are no pipelines that allow Russian gas to flow from Norway (our biggest source of imports) or via shipped Liquefied Natural Gas (which comes mainly from Qatar). Some gas of Russian origin may enter via pipelines from Belgium and the Netherlands. However Belgium has reported virtually no Russian gas imports over the past 3 years. The Netherlands does report some Russian imports, but we estimate Russian gas via this route would account for less than 1 per cent of the UK’s gas imports, and therefore much less than 1 per cent of our total gas supply.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577926/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-12T11:10:32.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577926/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577926/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-07","Natural Gas: Imports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much Russian gas is directly imported into the UK; and what percentage of overall national gas consumption that represents.","false","Biography information for Lord Truscott",,"Lord Truscott","HL1673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577927","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-19","<p>The UK Government opposes the use of the death penalty in all circumstances and takes any allegations of extrajudicial killings seriously. The Iranian Government has repeatedly denied that a mass execution took place, though we know that between July 1988 and January 1989 executions did take place. However, even with the recording and media reporting on the incident, we have no confirmation of the numbers involved.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577927/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T09:38:15.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577927/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577927/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","Iran: Political Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Baroness Anelay of St Johns on 6 September (HL Deb, col 936), and in the light of the release of the Montazeri audiotape regarding the massacres in Iran in 1988, whether it is still their position that there is little corroborated evidence of such a massacre taking place.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL1674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577928","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-28","<p>We have regularly raised with the Ethiopian Government at the highest levels our concerns about respect for civil and political rights as well as political prisoners. During his visit to Ethiopia in June the former Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), impressed upon Prime Minister Hailemariam Desalegn the need for more space for civil society and political dissent. Following the protests which have taken place in Ethiopia and the recent numbers of arrests of political opposition figures, we have raised with the Ethiopian Government the need for people currently detained who are facing criminal charges, to be allowed access to legal representation in order to defend themselves in a court of law. The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson) has raised the protests in his conversations with Ethiopian counterparts.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577928/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-28T15:34:24.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577928/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577928/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","Ethiopia: Political Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Ethiopia about the treatment of political detainees in that country.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577929","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-21","<p>Risks around international humanitarian law violations are a key part of our assessment against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria. A licence will not be issued for any country where we assess there is a clear risk that the items might be used in the commission of a serious violation of International Humanitarian Law.</p><p>Our export licensing system allows us to respond quickly to changed circumstances, with the option to revoke an export licence where we consider that there is a clear risk that the items being exported pursuant to that licence might be used in a serious violation of International Humanitarian Law.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577929/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-21T15:59:43.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577929/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577929/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","Arms Trade: Exports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what breaches of international humanitarian law in conflict situations constitute grounds for the revocation of arms export licences.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577930","Department of Health","false","2016-09-16","<p>Public Health England (PHE) produces figures for England and Wales based on the number of laboratory confirmed Lyme disease cases. They do not include cases that are diagnosed based on clinical symptoms alone e.g. the presence of a bull’s-eye rash. Confirmed figures from the United Kingdom Zoonoses report is shown in table 1.</p><p> </p><p>Table 1: Laboratory diagnosed Lyme disease cases, 2010-2014</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England and Wales</p></td><td><p>905</p></td><td><p>959</p></td><td><p>1,040</p></td><td><p>878</p></td><td><p>730</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK</p></td><td><p>1,213</p></td><td><p>1,189</p></td><td><p>1,249</p></td><td><p>1,060</p></td><td><p>955</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: UK Zoonoses Report, 2015</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>PHE does not produce official forecasts of the number of new Lyme disease cases that might be expected annually in England.</p><p> </p><p>PHE produces public information leaflets on how people can protect themselves against tick bites, and what to do after a tick bite. These are available on the Government’s website and copies of these are attached. Advice for patients suspecting they may have Lyme disease is available on the NHS Choices website and a copy of the relevant webpage is attached.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577930/answer","NHSChoices_Lyme_Disease_pages.pdf ; LymeDisease_SignsAndSymptoms.pdf ; Ticksandyourhealthinfoabouttickbites.pdf0.pdf","NHSChoices_Lyme_Disease_pages.pdf ; LymeDisease_SignsAndSymptoms.pdf ; Ticksandyourhealthinfoabouttickbites.pdf0.pdf","NHS Choices Lyme Disease ; Lyme Disease Signs & Symptoms ; Ticks and your health","NHS Choices Lyme Disease ; Lyme Disease Signs & Symptoms ; Ticks and your health",,"2016-09-16T11:13:21.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577930/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577930/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-07","Lyme Disease","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many new cases of Lyme disease have been diagnosed in each year since 2010; whether those figures are higher than the official forecasts of such cases; and if so, what action they are taking to raise awareness of Lyme disease.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577931","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-19","<p>The Armed Forces are meeting all of their current operational commitments. We routinely examine the implications of possible future activity for the Armed Forces and current deployments.</p>",,"Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577931/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T15:37:06.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577931/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577931/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Armed Forces","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of whether the army, the Royal Navy and the Royal Air Force each have the manpower to meet their current operational commitments; and what capacity each service has to meet additional commitments if required.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577932","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-14","<p>Whilst changes in the British Army have been discussed during regular meetings between UK and US officials, no formal representations of this nature have been made by the US Government.</p>",,"Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577932/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T16:39:26.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577932/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577932/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-07","Army","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the government of the USA has made representations to them about the manpower reductions in the British army.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577933","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-19","<p>We have been clear, as has the UN Security Council, that Daesh represent a threat to international peace and security. The UK has a shared interest with Libya and her neighbouring countries in the fight against terrorism, and we are committed to working together with them in a number of areas to combat the terrorist threat, including the risk that some Daesh fighters may seek to relocate from Sirte. Egypt is a vital partner in bringing peace and stability to Libya. As well as cooperating on counter-terrorism, we hold regular discussions on tackling the terrorist threat emanating from Libya, and are sharing expertise on border security. We are working with the Tunisian Government, in concert with other international partners, to secure the Libyan-Tunisian border. This includes the development of a border strategy with the government of Tunisia, targeted training of the border authorities, and provision of equipment to enhance their ability to police the border.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577933/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T09:26:38.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577933/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577933/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-07","Libya: Islamic State","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they are taking to assist with the formulation of a regional strategy and regional co-ordination to prevent IS fighters relocating from Libya to Tunisia and Egypt following the military operation in Libya to recapture Sirte.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577934","Home Office","false","2016-09-16","<p>All those who return from engaging in the conflict in Syria and Iraq can expect to be subject to investigation to determine if they have committed criminal offences abroad or represent a threat to our national security. Decisions to prosecute are taken, independently of Government, by the Crown Prosecution Service. Assessments are also made of the appropriateness of other forms of intervention, including referral to mental health services or to the Channel programme, for example. For reasons of national security, we do not comment further on action taken with respect to returners from Syria.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577934/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T13:14:07.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577934/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577934/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-07","Islamic State: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will provide details of the de-radicalisation programmes used for British Jihadis returning from Iraq and Syria, including (1) how many have undergone such programmes, (2) who delivers those programmes, and (3) the content of those programmes.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577935","HM Treasury","false","2016-09-19","<p>The IMF Executive Board discussed the report entitled <em>The IMF and the crises in Greece, Ireland, and Portugal</em> on 19 July 2016. The UK plays an active part in such dialogues. While we welcome the report, board discussions remain confidential until the minutes are made accessible three years after the meeting. The Chairman’s summing up, and the statement by the IMF Managing Director offering a response to the report’s recommendations, offer more information. They can be found on the Independent Evaluation Office’s (IEO) website.</p><p> </p><p>As the body which provides objective and independent evaluation on IMF issues, the work of the IEO is important in improving transparency, oversight and enhancing the learning culture at the Fund.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577935/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-19T09:22:25.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577935/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577935/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-09-07","International Monetary Fund","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the report published on 8 July by the Independent Evaluation Office of the International Monetary Fund, <i>The IMF and the crises in Greece, Ireland, and Portugal</i>.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577937","Department of Health","false","2016-09-14","<p>This is a matter for the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman.</p><p> </p><p>The Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman is independent of Government, and accountable to Parliament through the Public Administration and Constitutional Affairs Committee.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577937/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-14T16:36:01.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577937/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577937/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-07","Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman: Public Appointments","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when the report of the independent review commissioned by the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman (PHSO) into the adequacy of the procedures and governance arrangements that the organisation applied prior to the appointment of the deputy PHSO, Mr Mick Martin, will be published; and whether the full report will be released into the public domain, together with the PHSO's findings and actions.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL1683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577938","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-20","<p>Work is ongoing to establish the impact of the wind conditions at St Helena Airport, with a view to identifying the means to mitigate the impact of the wind shear on flight operations. At the same time work continues to identify options for commencing commercial air services, the timing of which depends on securing the right aircraft and regulatory approvals. We are aiming for these services to start as soon as possible.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577938/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-20T11:58:24.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577938/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577938/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-07","St Helena: Airports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress has been made on tackling the wind shear issue that is preventing the opening of St Helena’s airport to regular passenger flights; and when they anticipate that regular passenger flights will begin at that airport.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577939","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-20","<p>Whilst no specific discussions have been held with Gloucestershire County Council in respect to local highways maintenance budgets, the Department for Transport officials meet with officers from all local highway authorities in respect to a wide range of local transport issues on a regular basis.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has committed record levels of investment, over £6 billion, to highways maintenance up to 2020/21, including a Pothole Action Fund totalling £250 million in this Parliament. From this funding we are allocating over £95 million to the council to help improve the condition of the local roads for which Gloucestershire County Council are responsible.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577939/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-20T12:46:13.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577939/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577939/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-07","Roads: Gloucestershire","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with Gloucestershire County Council regarding the budget required to repair local roads in the county.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577940","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-16","<p>The UK Government is engaged in regular discussions with partner Governments, other donors, the private sector and key stakeholders to help target support to build the resilience of communities vulnerable to the impacts of climate change, for example through coastal flooding and tropical storms. At the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting in 2015 the UK led an initiative to focus attention on the vulnerability of Commonwealth small island states.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577940/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-16T11:02:32.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577940/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577940/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-07","Climate Change: Islands","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have held with international partners on tackling the difficulties being experienced by low-lying island states due to rises in sea levels and the increased frequency of tropical storms.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577941","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-20","<p>As announced on 15 September, the Government has decided to proceed with the Hinkley Point C nuclear power station subject to acceptance by the developer of the additional protections detailed in the announcement.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577941/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-20T15:26:13.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577941/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577941/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-07","Hinkley Point C Power Station","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they will announce a decision on whether they plan to proceed with Hinkley Point C nuclear power station.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577942","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>The UK package of support for the uptake and manufacture of ultra low emission vehicles (ULEVs) is already one of the most comprehensive in the world. This Government is investing over £600 million this Parliament, including a tax regime favourable towards less polluting vehicles, to ensure that almost all cars and vans are zero emission vehicles by 2050. We expect to make further announcements on this agenda in due course.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577942/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-21T11:21:00.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577942/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577942/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-07","Electric Vehicles","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what further measures they plan to take to encourage the take-up of electric or hybrid vehicles and to deter the use of petrol and diesel powered vehicles.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577943","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-21","<p>We will take the necessary Parliamentary steps for domestic approval to enable ratification shortly.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577943/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-21T15:35:25.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577943/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/577943/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-07","Climate Change Convention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what actions they are taking to ratify the Paris agreement on climate change.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL1689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582177","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-13","<p>The Government has been working closely with industry to provide all the support we can during these difficult times.</p><p> </p><p>We have made significant progress in addressing the challenges faced by the industry and we have convened a Steel Council to ensure our continued support is targeted in the right areas.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582177/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T13:46:53.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582177/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582177/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-07","Iron and Steel: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to improve the confidence of suppliers and customers in the future of the UK steel industry.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","906297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582178","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-13","<p>The financing of HPC is a matter for EDF.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582178/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T13:52:20.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582178/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582178/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-07","Hinkley Point C Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has made an assessment of alternative plans for the development of Hinkley Point in the event that China withdraw its planned investment in that project.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","906293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582179","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-13","<p>We are proud of our track record on investment. Nearly £52 billion has been invested since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>In the Budget we announced £730m of annual support, for 15 year contracts, for less established renewable electricity projects, including offshore wind; and an increase in the renewable heat incentive to £1.15bn.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582179/answer",,,,,,"2016-09-13T13:59:08.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582179/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582179/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-07","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps the Government is taking to promote the British renewable energy industry.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","906289"
